28/06/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Zef Mazi, the Albanian ambassador to the OSCE, is running for the post of OSCE Secretary General in elections to be held later this year. Government spokesperson Aldrin Dalipi said Friday (25 June) that Tirana supports Mazi's nomination, adding that his 17 years of diplomatic experience have won him respect not only from OSCE, but also from the wider international community.
In other news, Albanian Chief of Army Staff Lieutenant General Pellumb Qazimi met with his Macedonian counterpart, Major General Gjorgji Bojadijev, on Friday. They praised the current level of military relations and discussed the joint goals of NATO and EU integration. (ATA - 28/06/04; ATA - 25/06/04)
